# List of heritage sites in Graaff-Reinet

This is a list of the heritage sites in Graaff-Reinet as recognised by the South African Heritage Resources Agency.
Architectural style: Victorian (77) with Karoo-type extension (75). Type of site: House Current use: Residential (2 units). These buildings, with their Georgian Karoo style and Victorian features, which date mainly from the nineteenth century, form an integral part of the historical and architectural core of Graaff-Reinet, which was founded in 1785.
